The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Madurai, June 8 (PTI): A man poisoned more than 30 dogs to death in Tamil Nadu after one of his pet goats was killed by a dog.          
	He was fined Rs 20,000 by the local panchayat after the dog owners lodged a complaint. The sum was distributed among the dog owners, officials said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The environment ministry is considering banning elephants from circuses following reports that circus owners do not comply with the provisions of the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act. Such a ban is in effect in Sweden, Austria, Costa Rica, Finland and Singapore. Indian circuses are already banned from exhibiting tigers, lions and monkeys.                  
	Nagpur (PTI): Three persons were arrested for posing as late actor Raj Kapoors relatives and trying to sell 25 acres of land owned by his brother-in-law in the city, police said on Sunday. Durga Pandurang Rokde, 35, Nitika Rao, 32, and Satyapal Kewalramani, 52, tried to sell land that belonged to the late Charanjeet Sial. The potential buyer suspected a fraud and informed the police.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): The Bombay High Court has held that death caused by falling off a train qualifies for compensation under the Railways Act. The claim was filed by a couple, who lost their son in a train accident. The court held that Central Railway would have to pay them Rs 4 lakh, as determined by a claims tribunal.                  
	Thimpu (PTI): Twelve Indian construction workers were killed on Saturday night in Bhutan when a boulder hit the truck they were travelling in, police said. The truck was negotiating a narrow stretch of wet road. The workers were returning from the construction site.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): Maharani Karthika Tirunal Lakshmibai, the seniormost member and queen mother of the Travancore royal family, died in hospital here on Sunday. She was 92 and is survived by three children.                                                                                                                         
